      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 97,
      "message": "Agreed, we don't know how many of the transitions are for new vs existing vs deleted handles.\n\nFor example, for 100 new ADVISED handles: newCmHandles will be 100, compositeStatePerCmHandleId will be empty. For 100 DELETED handles: both newCmHandles and compositeStatePerCmHandleId will be empty, etc.\n\nBasically we will be wasting memory most of the time by pre-allocating.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
